levels/
Level JSON API Map (Version 1.0 Freeze)

This folder contains every playable level.

The Match-3 engine never hardcodes a level. Every aspect of gameplay is loaded from a level JSON file.

Folder
levels/
    level001.json
    level002.json
    ...
    level050.json

Future versions can simply add:

level051.json
level052.json
...

without modifying the engine.

Common JSON Structure

Every level uses the same schema.

{
    "level_id": 1,
    "name": "",
    "description": "",
    "difficulty": "",
    "board": {},
    "moves": {},
    "objectives": [],
    "tile_pool": {},
    "powerups": {},
    "obstacles": {},
    "rewards": {},
    "tutorial": {},
    "story": {},
    "audio": {},
    "background": {},
    "settings": {},
    "metadata": {}
}
level_id

Unique level number.

"level_id": 1
name

Display name.

"name": "Level 1"
description

Optional.

"description": "Learn the basics."
difficulty

Possible values

TUTORIAL
EASY
MEDIUM
HARD
BOSS

Example

"difficulty": "TUTORIAL"
board

Defines the game board.

{
    "rows": 8,
    "columns": 8,
    "tile_size": 96,
    "spawn_points": [],
    "blocked_cells": [],
    "locked_cells": []
}
rows
"rows": 8
columns
"columns": 8
tile_size
"tile_size": 96
spawn_points

Optional custom spawn positions.

[
    { "x":0,"y":0 },
    { "x":1,"y":0 }
]
blocked_cells

Cells that cannot contain tiles.

[
    { "x":3,"y":4 },
    { "x":4,"y":4 }
]
locked_cells

Cells that start locked.

[
    { "x":2,"y":2 }
]
moves
{
    "total": 30
}
objectives

Array.

[
    { ... },
    { ... }
]

Each objective uses

{
    "type":"",
    "target":"",
    "amount":0
}
Objective Types
COLLECT_ITEMS
COLLECT_EVIDENCE
DESTROY_OBSTACLES
UNLOCK_DOORS
DEFUSE_BOMBS
REACH_SCORE
RESCUE_BABY
SURVIVE
CLEAR_ALL_JELLY

Example

{
    "type":"COLLECT_ITEMS",
    "target":"PHONE",
    "amount":20
}
tile_pool

Tiles allowed to spawn.

{
    "tiles":[
        "KEY",
        "PHONE",
        "RECORDER",
        "CLOCK"
    ],
    "weights":[
        30,
        30,
        20,
        20
    ]
}
powerups

Powerups enabled in this level.

{
    "enabled":true,
    "available":[
        "ROCKET",
        "BOMB",
        "THUNDER"
    ]
}
obstacles

Obstacles placed at the start of the level.

{
    "items":[
        {
            "type":"CHAIN",
            "x":2,
            "y":4,
            "health":2
        }
    ]
}
rewards

Rewards for completing the level.

{
    "coins":100,
    "stars":3,
    "first_try_bonus":50,
    "perfect_bonus":100,
    "powerups":[]
}
tutorial

Tutorial configuration.

{
    "enabled":true,
    "steps":[]
}

Each tutorial step

{
    "message":"Swipe these tiles.",
    "highlight":[
        { "x":3,"y":4 },
        { "x":4,"y":4 }
    ]
}
story

Story integration.

"story":
{
    "before_level":"",
    "after_level":"",
    "first_clear":"",
    "return_to_map":true
}

Either value may be omitted if no story is played.

audio

Level-specific audio.

{
    "music":"level_theme_01",
    "victory":"victory",
    "game_over":"game_over"
}
background

Background art.

{
    "image":"city_day",
    "parallax":false
}
settings

Optional gameplay modifiers.

{
    "time_limit":0,
    "allow_shuffle":true,
    "allow_boosters":true
}

A time limit of 0 means the level is move-based rather than timed.

metadata

Internal information.

{
    "version":1,
    "author":"Save The Baby",
    "notes":""
}
Level Progression Responsibilities
level001.json

Purpose

First tutorial level
Teach swipe-to-swap
No obstacles
Very easy objectives
level002.json

Purpose

Continue tutorial
Introduce simple matching
Reinforce board mechanics
Levels 003–010

Purpose

Complete tutorial
Introduce objectives
Increase board complexity gradually
Levels 011–020

Purpose

Introduce basic obstacles
Require more strategic play
Levels 021–035

Purpose

Introduce powerup combinations
More complex board layouts
Multi-objective levels
Levels 036–049

Purpose

Advanced mechanics
Mixed obstacles
Higher difficulty
Complex objective combinations
level050.json

Purpose

Boss level
Final challenge of Version 1
Story climax
Leads directly to ending.json
Level Flow
level001.json
      │
      ▼
level002.json
      │
      ▼
...
      │
      ▼
level050.json
Frozen Responsibilities
File(s)	Responsibility
level001.json	First tutorial level
level002.json	Continue tutorial
level003–010.json	Complete tutorial and introduce objectives
level011–020.json	Introduce obstacles
level021–035.json	Introduce powerups and combinations
level036–049.json	Advanced gameplay and difficulty
level050.json	Boss level and campaign finale

This freezes the JSON schema and responsibilities for every file under:

levels/

All gameplay systems (such as LevelManager, BoardGenerator, RewardManager, StoryManager, and BoardManager) should read level data from this schema without requiring changes to the file format during Version 1.